  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors nominally addressed; however, two factors are carried as not-assessed on the grounds that the corresponding activities were considered beyond the scope of the current submission phase. Model risk level is 3 (Medium-High), which means the absence of assessed status for these factors materially weakens overall credibility.",
